BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NLHJEmbWvMD58LdbtO0gT
SUMMARY:Chuckle Bucket Tuesday @ Club Comedy Seattle (Open Mic)
DTSTAMP:20260306T004541Z
DTSTART:20260318T020000Z
DESCRIPTION:Club Comedy Seattle hosts Chuckle Bucket Tuesday each week. The
	 luck of the bucket rules the night. Comics drop their name in and hope to
	 be drawn for one of the spots on the list to tell jokes. It's fun\, fast-
	paced and will keep you laughing hard on your Tuesday night.\n\nDoor 7:00P
	M/Show 7:30PM\n\nAdmission: $7 \\+ $0.35 City Of Seattle Admission Tax\n\n
	21\\+ With Valid ID REQUIRED for entry. NO REFUNDS.\n\nFYI: If you have a 
	large party it's easier for us to seat you all together if you purchase al
	l the tickets under one name.\n\n.\n\nClub Comedy Seattle FAQ\n\nIs there 
	an age/ID requirement?\n\nYes. We are strictly 21\\+ and valid physical ID
	 is REQUIRED For Entry\n\nIs Seating First Come/First Served?\n\nYes. The 
	room is all two top tables and we seat guests in the order in which they a
	rrive.\n\nCan I reserve a table for a group?\n\nWe do not take reservation
	s for tables\, but groups can arrive early to secure seating together.\n\n
	Are tickets available at the door if an event is sold out online?\n\nIf an
	 event is sold out online there are no tickets available at the door.\n\nW
	hat are the club’s hours of operation?\n\nThe club is open Tuesday to Sund
	ay. Doors open a half hour before each show.\n\nWhat is the Parking like?\
	n\nGenerally there is street parking available in the blocks surrounding t
	he club. There are also affordable parking lots on 16th Ave E right around
	 the block from the club along with other easy options in the neighborhood
	\n\nIs there a dress code?\n\nThere is no formal dress code\, but we recom
	mend smart casual attire.\n\nCan I bring food or drinks?\n\nOutside food a
	nd drinks are not allowed. We have a full bar and a menu available for you
	r enjoyment.\n\nWhat if I can't make it and need to cancel my ticket?\n\nA
	ll ticket sales are final. However\, if you can’t make it\, please contact
	 us through Eventbrite in advance\, and we’ll do our best to accommodate y
	ou.\n\nWill there be an opener for the headliner?\n\nYes\, headliner shows
	 feature a lineup of comedians\, including a host\, an opener\, and the he
	adliner.\n\nWill the comics talk to me like I see in online videos all the
	 time?\n\nMost likely they won't. Crowd work videos are popular for postin
	g online\, but crowd work doesn't generally happen at the online frequency
	 in live comedy show situations. Some comics do engage the crowd as part o
	f their regular set and it's generally always fun and more about making fu
	n of themselves than making fun of the crowd.\n\nHow can I get on the Chea
	p Laughs Open Mic On Wednesdays?\n\nSubmissions for spots on the Wednesday
	 Cheap Laughs Open Mic are accepted only on the Tuesday before between 12:
	00AM and 11:59PM via email at openmic@clubcomedyseattle.com\n\nDo you offe
	r group discounts?\n\nYes\, we offer discounts for groups of ten or more. 
	Please contact us for more details.\n\nCan I meet the comedians after the 
	show?\n\nMeet-and-greet opportunities vary by event. Please ask staff for 
	details after the show.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/c
	huckle-bucket-tuesday-club-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18244225/2026-03-17T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/chuckle-bucket-tuesday-cl
	ub-comedy-seattle-open-mic/18244225/2026-03-17T00
LOCATION:Club Comedy Seattle\, 328 15th Ave E\, Seattle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:se70m50VDR70-NkuPH6P0
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260306T004542Z
DTSTART:20260318T070000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-18T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-03-18T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
